%% Diagram: Scroll restoration on back-navigation
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Feed as Feed Page
    participant Router as SPA Router
    participant Store as sessionStorage
    participant API as Backend

    Note over Feed: history.scrollRestoration = manual
    User->>Feed: scrolls and opens an item
    Feed->>Store: save pageCount, scrollY,<br/>anchorItemId, timestamp
    Feed->>Router: navigate to detail route
    Router-->>User: detail view rendered

    User->>Router: browser Back
    Router-->>Feed: popstate (manual mode:<br/>browser does not auto-restore)
    Feed->>Store: read scroll state
    alt state present and < 5 min old
        Feed->>API: refetch pages 1..pageCount<br/>(or hydrate from cache)
        API-->>Feed: items
        Feed->>Feed: scrollToIndex(anchorItemId)
        Feed->>Feed: nudge by measured offset
        Feed->>Store: clear key
    else state missing or stale
        Feed->>Feed: render top of feed
    end
    Feed-->>User: visible position restored
